'''
    Topic: Variables
    Author: Anup Chando Dhrubo
'''

# Variables are created when we assign value to it
# No need to declare any type of variable
var1 = 4
var2 = "Dhrubo"
print (var1, var2)

# Change var2 value
var2 = "Rudro"
print (var2)

# Var2 is of string type, change var2 value to another type
var2 = 5
print (var2)

'''
    Casting: If we want to specify the data type of a variable, this can be done with casting.
'''

x = str(3)  # 3 is an integer type value, but now it is of string type
print (type(x))  # type(variable_name) ; this returns the type of variable
